headline.print_headline: Premier Says He’ll Resign, Surprising New Zealand
headline.main: John Key, New Zealand’s Prime Minister, Says He Will Step Down

snippet: The 55-year-old prime minister, of the conservative National Party, has been in office since 2008, and his tenure has been seen as generally stable and free of controversy....
lead_paragraph: The 55-year-old prime minister, of the conservative National Party, has been in office since 2008, and his tenure has been seen as generally stable and free of controversy.
